RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 15200. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $6,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WESTERN CHARM ran with a steady gain in the middle of the pack took the lead late into the stretch during a strong closing drive. ROLL TO RICHES ran evenly behind the leader pressed the pace and wore down his foe. BALD IS BEAUTIFUL ran in the middle of the pack then on the stretch had a good kick to pass a couple foes. AHEAD OF TIME KID ran at the back of the pack and at the sixteenth pole made a strong rally to pass many foes. AL GRANO D ORO had good early speed then shuffled back as the race progressed. QUEENS EFFORT ran in the middle of the pack with a steady pace. TOMMY'S UP set the early pace but the pace was pressed continuously and was wore down by the start of the stretch and faded mid stretch. PIP PIP ran at the back of the pack with an even pace throughout the race. F J COLIMA shuffled to the back on the turn then just maintained on the stretch. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 19100. FOR REGISTERED NEW MEXICO BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 14 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Condition Eligibility Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUVAL ran at the back of the pack then started to gain speed at the start of the stretch getting the edge over foe at wire. D C GUN RUNNER ran off pace, slightly pressed the pace just missed at the wire. DIABOLICAL PACKAGE set the early pace then was caught mid turn to duel until the sixteenth pole, and maintained for show. MICKEYS GOLD ran in the middle of the pack evenly throughout the race. MISS TRICKY INDY good early speed then shuffled back after the first quarter, but coming on to the stretch tried to rally and but ran out of track to pass foes. TIZ'A STELLAR DUDE ran evenly at the beginning of the race then hung mid stretch. DINOS DA DADDY had good early speed but faded to the back, but at the end of the race they passed a tired foe. ZESTY JAZZMAN ran at the back of the pack had a slight gain on the turn then shuffled back coming onto the stretch. ALL YOUR JAZZ ran evenly but just wasn't enough and ran out of gas at the sixteenth pole. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 70. Allowance Purse 33000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IT'S SAUL RIGHT ran at the back of the pack then coming on to the stretch made a strong closing drive down the middle of the track. NATION OF LAWS ran at the front pressed the pace, wore down foe mid stretch then missed the win by three and three quarter lengths. M G BIG MARIA ran in the middle pack on the outside, took the turn five wide and took the open outside path to claim a podium spot. CAIRO MOON ran in the middle of the pack then mid stretch had a late rally to pass a foe. WILLOWMYGIRL ran at the front of the pack but after the turn hung in the middle of the stretch. ILOVEHER ran at the back of the pack then right before the stretch had a slight kick to start passing a foe further down the stretch. WHAT A WAY TO GO ran at the back of the pack and passed tired foes at the end of the race. CHASING DIVINITY ran even in the middle of the pack then faded at the start of the stretch. FIRST ZAP trailed throughout the race and finally passed a foe at the wire. PRINCESS KITTEN had good early speed took the lead briefly, but coming on to the stretch started to show signs of running out of gas then faded hard at the one eighth pole. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Manzano S. ALBUQUERQUE RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 74. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR TWO YEAR OLDS. By subscription of $200 to nominate, an additional $400 to enter. non-winners of a sweepstakes In 2023 allowed.2 lbs. Field limited to twelve (12) starters with horses preferred by lifetime earnings at time of closing nominations. W eight.120 lbs. Fillies.117 lbs. Nominations close Wednesday, October 4, 2023 at 2:00 PM. RACE WILL BE LASIX FREE. (A Trophy will be presented to the winning Owner).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CANDY AISLE ran off pace from the leader then coming on to the stretch in the four path dueling GREASE MISSLE ended up passing foe and drew off late stretch. SALSATION had early speed then going into the turn GREASE MISSLE pushed in and caused a check going into the turn, but took an outside path to make up ground and pass the foe that caused an issue earlier in the race. GREASE MISSLE ran in the four path got slightly a head drifted in causing foes to check going into the turn. MY GOOD GOOD BOY ran at the back then took an inside path with a rally to pass slowed foes. LITE RANCHIN KID had good speed early on then GREASE MISSLE pushed in and caused a check going into the turn, was on the rail but never regained. FERRARI RED had good speed leaving the gate and down the backstretch then GREASE MISSLE pushed in and caused a check going into the turn, unfortunately, FERRARI RED never regained. THERE WAS A STEWARDS INQUIRY WHERE GREASE MISSLE CROSSED IN FRONT OF THE THREE FOES BETWEEN THEM AND THE RAIL, THE STEWARDS DETEREMINED THERE WILL BE NO CHANGE IN ORDER OF FINISH. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.
